==English==

===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''[[avis]]'', {{F.}} ''[[avis]]''; + {{OF.}} ''[[vis]]'', from {{L.}} ''[[visum]]'' seemed, seen; really past participle of ''[[videre]]'' to see, so that ''[[vis]]'' meant that which has seemed best.  See [[vision]], and confer ''[[avise]], [[advise]]''.

